# Cloudflare Workers Static Assets _redirects.
#
# SITE IN REBUILD (2026-05-19): full-site holder. No redirect rules.
# The holder is served for every non-matching path via the Worker's
# not_found_handling = "single-page-application" (wrangler.jsonc),
# plus the deploy step prunes pitch/blog/etc out of dist so there are
# no old assets to match. A `/* /index.html 200` rule here is INVALID
# (Cloudflare rejects it as an infinite loop, code 10021) — do not
# re-add it. The 2026-05-19 holder is gone (site rebuilt); specific
# path rules below are live. Instrument (app.neverranked.com) is a
# separate Worker, unaffected.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# Cold-email CTA redirect (restored 2026-07-18).
#
# WHY: every outreach email links to the 2-label apex /check on purpose.
# The 3-label check.neverranked.com trips SpamAssassin URI_TRY_3LD
# (~2 spam pts, the biggest measured content deduction, mail-tester
# 7/10), so the email cannot link there directly. This 302 forwards the
# apex /check to the scanner. Cloudflare passes the incoming query to a
# destination that has none, so ?url=<domain>&utm_* arrives intact and
# the recipient lands on the scanner pre-loaded with their own domain.
#
# This rule was dropped in the 2026-05-19 rebuild and not restored,
# while both generators kept emitting /check links, so every outreach
# link 404'd. Specific path rule, not the forbidden /* catch-all.
/check   https://check.neverranked.com/   302

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# Auth-link reputation redirect (added 2026-06-01).
#
# WHY: customer sign-in emails must link to a domain Gmail trusts.
# app.neverranked.com is a new, uncrawlable subdomain with low Google
# reputation, so Gmail flags "sign in" links to it as dangerous. This
# root domain (neverranked.com) is crawlable and has real reputation,
# so auth emails link here and we 302 to the dashboard's verify route.
#
# Cloudflare forwards the incoming query string to a destination that
# has no query string of its own, so ?token=...[&next=...] passes through
# intact. This is a specific path rule, not the forbidden /* catch-all,
# so it is safe alongside the SPA holder.
/signin  https://app.neverranked.com/auth/verify  302

